reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice universal fit car seat covers. 2003 Saturn Vue
reviews.reviewText: First off, I did not end up using the clips. I mainly have the trunk down because I am a fur-mom x2 (no 2 legged children); except for the neighborhood kids I take to church on Wednesday and Sunday, then the seats are back up in the sitting position.Back to the clips! Seeing as I have the seats down and pups in the back (American Staffordshire Terrier and Blue nose pit) I didn't want them walking on them, so they don't hurt the paws or snag on the felt interior. Also, the last picture I put a trunk cover down and didn't want that torn.For the non-dog car rider people these clips go at the end of the elastic and it was tough for me to pull the elastic under the crevice of the seat and trunk then stretch and clip. One end is the loop the other is like a tighter L-shape and I would use pliers and close them into each other to fasten more securely. The clips work but not sure how long it will stay and not pup moving the seat from up to down position. Therefore, I secured mine with zip ties! They seem to fix it all just like electrical tape! j/k. The zip ties wont hurt the pups paws; I could give it more slack in the stretch attachments that come on the seat covers and it doesn't feel so tight that it is gonna rip them.To be honest; that was my hardest part. Getting the backseat part on and then making sure they were nice and snug around the back part. Oh, and the front seats have a velcro snap to secure under the seat. Have to go under both sides of seats and feed them through the seat adjuster then velcro it.The part about removing the headrest and cutting small holes to fit the headrest back over and also cut holes for the seatbelt snaps was easy. For the head rest cut a small pinch out about the size of a dime and that is perfect to fit it nicely. The seat belts about the size of a quarter and you can wiggle them through and if it gets too tough just cut a tad bit more and they fit nice.My front seats look a little baggy in the picture because I have arm rest on my seats. I am going to got back and do the same like the headrest. I will remove the arm rest; pull the car seat cover into place taunt and then cut a small hole and put the arm rest back on. I was just getting tired and the rain was coming. Otherwise you could just cut a vertical line long enough to slip around the arm rest bar and down to the bottom of seat but that could be a lot of material cut versus a small size dime hole like the headrest.I also purchased the product for less than the NEW price. I picked the like new for about $13 dollars and they look brand new? I don't know if it was because the box appeared opened then taped back but mine look brand new and had no cuts or tears in them. What a deal!Item arrived quickly packaged nicely with no damage. Again, budget friendly for my fixed income disability budget. Seats are protected from dog hair and a quick spill of a drink if it happens. Got them in my favorite color too! Very pleased; would order again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars For the price it’s not bad at all
reviews.reviewText: For the price, definitely not bad. The material is very fragile so be careful when you’re pulling on the cords to connect. The front seat cover were the easiest to install and required no cutting of material. The back seat were the hardest to install and I don’t think I did too bad on them. I could only tuck in the material of the bottom cover, but was able to hook the top part to at least give it the presence of a good fit. Cutting the fabric was simple and I didn’t need to cut much, just enough for the seat belt buckles to fit. I bought these just to protect my leather seats in my Ford Fiesta since they still look like new.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nicely priced, good looking seat covers
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these for son’s vehicle for Christmas. He has a 2017 Buick encore. It said they would fit. I started with the back seat and they fit and looked really good. They were comfortable, well made, and the price was great. However, when I got to the front driver seat, a problem occurred. Unfortunately it didn’t fit because the encore has an arm rest for the driver seat. If I put it up, it fit, but my son likes the arm rest. So I had to return these. I would recommend them though for the price, fit, comfort, and look.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Do not Fit 2012 Honda CRV
reviews.reviewText: These seat covers do not fit a Honda CRV 2012 EX. The Headrest covers fit fine, the front seat covers are alright for the seat back, except for they cover the seat back pocket. The seat bottom is ill fitting, shows the hem and gathering and shifts / bunches as it is an incorrect fit. The elastic meant to gather the cover around the seat bottom for a "custom" fit is not in an accessible location for the CRV and even when fastened is in the wrong location to help the seat cover fit correctly.The seat cover is thin, cheap neoprene like fabric with an unpleasant feeling to the touch.Caveat - I did not attempt to install the back seat cover as the front seat covers do not fit well enough to bother with the back.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Overall good but not correct fit for 2022 Buick Encore GX rear bench back cover
reviews.reviewText: Per instructions, need to remove rear seat headrests which I cannot do for 2022 Buick Encore GX so I used rear bench seat and headrest covers but have left off rear bench (vertical) back cover piece. In future I may cut cover, fit around headrest posts, and sew back together in place. Instructions also say to remove front bucket seat headrests (which are also un-removable on this car), but openings in front seat covers fit over both driver and passenger headrests so front seat covers can be installed. They are a little loose but black/gray colors are perfect match for interior so I'm happy enough.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good at first but lacking in durability
reviews.reviewText: Bought this for my 2016 Kia forte to protect the seats from my messy self. They went on fairly easily. I don’t like the way the headrest covers fit, baggy, so I leafy them off. I was forever adjusting the front drivers seat cover. Before I got in and after I got in and again upon exiting the vehicle. Eventually, maybe a month or two later a whole began to form along the seams. Overall these were ok for the low price but if you’re looking for something nice that will last awhile, this isn’t it
